http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/PWD-engineer-caught-taking-bribe/article14014612.ece

A junior engineer with the Public Works Department was arrested for allegedly taking bribe, the Delhi Police said on Friday.Indramani Maurya was caught ‘red-handed’ taking a bribe of Rs 10,000 from a contractor who wanted a bill for a school building passed, said a senior officer with the Delhi Police’s vigilance branch that conducted the operation.Maurya had allegedly demanded Rs. 50,000 from the contractor upon which the latter approached the vigilance branch. A trap was laid at the PWD office in Alipur on Friday and the suspect nabbed, said the police.